pe="date" label="Date" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true" display="localdateshort" UTC="true">20130315T18:00:00</Date><Author type="string" label="Author's Name" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Hayden Coombs</Author><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Height=""><![CDATA[<p>Money allocated for Thomas E. Ricks Grants is still available for 2013.</p>
<p>The Thomas E. Ricks Endowment was created to support BYU-Idaho faculty in their enrichment, retraining, and teaching efforts. All campus faculty are eligible to apply for research, travel, seminar, or any other grant that will directly benefit students.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Thomas E. Ricks Grants are an important part of campus faculty development at this university and can be used to:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Broaden Knowledge -</strong><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Grants allow faculty to gather valuable expertise to share with the larger faculty and to instruct the student body.</span></li>
<li><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Conduct Research &amp; Share Creative Works&nbsp;-</strong><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Grants allow faculty to share their works and findings at professional conferences and workshops.</span></li>
<li><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Recertify &amp; Develop Professionally&nbsp;-</strong><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Grants provide funding to obtain industry certifications and training that impact classroom activities.</span></li>
<li><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Master Dynamic Content &amp; Stay Relevant&nbsp;-</strong><strong style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Grants help faculty keep up-to-date in their fields so curriculum will remain current.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">The deadlines for each semester are November 1</span><sup style="line-height: 1.4em;">st</sup><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">, March 1</span><sup style="line-height: 1.4em;">st</sup><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">, and June 1</span><sup style="line-height: 1.4em;">st</sup><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">. Requests for funding can be made up to 18 months in advance of your project start date. In order to assist the highest number of faculty, applicants who have not received any money in the past three years will be given highest priority.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">To submit a proposal, please complete the&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/instructional_development/documents/TER%20Application1.pdf" style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Grant Proposal Form</a><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">.&nbsp;Please limit your response so as not to exceed the space provided on the proposal form. Do not include attachments. Once you have completed the proposal, make sure your department chair and dean provide comments and their signatures. Completed proposals (scanned copies will be accepted) should be forwarded to: &nbsp; </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Maria Nate<br /></span><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">Instructional Development<br /></span><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">350 McKay<br /></span><a href="mailto:natem@byui.edu" style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">natem@byui.edu</a></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.4em;">If you have any additional questions, please visit the Thomas E. Ricks Grant Website, or contact Maria Nate using the email address listed above.</span></p>]]></BodyCopy><xPower Type="Component" Component="x35693" Name="HighlightedLinks" label="Highlighted Links" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="HighlightedLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="News" label="News" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="NewsNavigationComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="List" List="xpowercomponent_ContentSnippet" Name="ContentSnippet" label="Content Snippet" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false" Component="" CompTypes="ContentSnippet"><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ContentSnippet" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false" CompTypes="ContentSnippet"/></xPower><xPower Type="Navigation" StartPage="x5" MaxDepth="" MaxNodes="" GenerationOrder="down" Navigation="Ancestors" Query="" Name="AncestorNavigation" label="Ancestor Navigation" readonly="true" hidden="true" required="false" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="x19084" Name="SiteControl" label="Site Control" readonly="true" hidden="true" required="false" CompTypes="SiteControl"/></NewsDetail>
